210template <class T> class Handle {
211 public:
215 V8_INLINE Handle() : val_(0) {}
216
227 template <class S> V8_INLINE Handle(Handle<S> that)
228 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
234 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
235 }
236
240 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
241
245 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
246
247 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
248
249 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
250
257 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Handle<S>& that) const {
258 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
259 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
260 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
261 if (b == 0) return false;
262 return *a == *b;
263 }
264
265 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
266 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
267 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
268 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
269 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
270 if (b == 0) return false;
271 return *a == *b;
272 }
273
280 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Handle<S>& that) const {
281 return !operator==(that);
282 }
283
284 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
285 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
286 return !operator==(that);
287 }
288
289 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Handle<T> Cast(Handle<S> that) {
290#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
291 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
292 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
293 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Handle<T>();
294#endif
295 return Handle<T>(T::Cast(*that));
296 }
297
298 template <class S> V8_INLINE Handle<S> As() {
299 return Handle<S>::Cast(*this);
300 }
301
302 V8_INLINE static Handle<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Handle<T> that) {
303 return New(isolate, that.val_);
304 }
305 V8_INLINE static Handle<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
306 const PersistentBase<T>& that) {
307 return New(isolate, that.val_);
308 }
309
310 private:
311 friend class Utils;
312 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
313 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
314 template<class F> friend class Handle;
315 template<class F> friend class Local;
316 template <class F>
317 friend class MaybeLocal;
318 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
319 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
320 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
321 friend Handle<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
322 friend Handle<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
323 friend Handle<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
324 friend Handle<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);
325 friend class Context;
326 friend class HandleScope;
327 friend class Object;
328 friend class Private;
329
333 V8_INLINE explicit Handle(T* val) : val_(val) {}
334
335 V8_INLINE static Handle<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
336
337 T* val_;
338};

435
436 template <class S>

447 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);

452};

455// Eternal handles are set-once handles that live for the life of the isolate.

457 public:

461 Set(isolate, handle);

471};

474static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;

477template <typename T>
478class WeakCallbackInfo {
479 public:
480 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
481
482 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
483 void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
484 Callback* callback)
485 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
486 for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
487 internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
488 }
489 }
490
491 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
492 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
493 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
494
495 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
496 void* GetInternalField1()) const {
497 return internal_fields_[0];
498 }
499 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
500 void* GetInternalField2()) const {
501 return internal_fields_[1];
502 }
503
504 bool IsFirstPass() const { return callback_ != nullptr; }
505
506 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
507 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
508 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
509 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
510 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
511 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
512 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
513
514 private:
515 Isolate* isolate_;
516 T* parameter_;
517 Callback* callback_;
518 void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
519};

621 "use WeakCallbackInfo version",

631 // Phantom persistents work like weak persistents, except that the pointer to
632 // the object being collected is not available in the finalization callback.
633 // This enables the garbage collector to collect the object and any objects
634 // it references transitively in one GC cycle. At the moment you can either
635 // specify a parameter for the callback or the location of two internal
636 // fields in the dying object.
637 template <typename P>
638 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
639 "use SetWeak",
640 void SetPhantom(P* parameter,
641 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
642 int internal_field_index1 = -1,
643 int internal_field_index2 = -1));
644
645 template <typename P>
646 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
647 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
648 WeakCallbackType type);
649
650 template<typename P>
651 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
652
653 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
654 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }

662 V8_INLINE void MarkIndependent();
663
672 V8_INLINE void MarkPartiallyDependent();
673
674 V8_INLINE bool IsIndependent() const;
675
677 V8_INLINE bool IsNearDeath() const;
678
680 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
681
686 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
687
692 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;

694 private:
695 friend class Isolate;

697 template<class F> friend class Handle;
698 template<class F> friend class Local;

707 friend class Object;

809 Copy(that);
810 return *this;
811 }

818 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
819 }

830 }
831
832 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
833 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() { // NOLINT

835 }

857template <class T>
858class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {

870 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Handle<S> that)

879 template <class S>
880 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)

882 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);

896 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
897 if (this != &rhs) {
898 this->Reset();
899 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
900 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
901 }
902 return *this;
903 }
907 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); }

1161 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1162 enum BufferPolicy {
1163 BufferNotOwned,
1164 BufferOwned
1165 };
1166
1167 CachedData()
1168 : data(NULL),
1169 length(0),
1170 rejected(false),
1171 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1172
1173 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1174 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1175 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1176 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1177 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1178 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1179 ~CachedData();
1180 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1181 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1182 const uint8_t* data;
1183 int length;
1184 bool rejected;
1185 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1186
1187 private:
1188 // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1189 CachedData(const CachedData&);
1190 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&);
1191 };

4879struct JitCodeEvent {
4880 enum EventType {
4881 CODE_ADDED,
4882 CODE_MOVED,
4883 CODE_REMOVED,
4884 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
4885 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
4886 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
4887 };
4888 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
4889 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
4890 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
4891 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
4892 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
4893 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
4894
4895 // Type of event.
4896 EventType type;
4897 // Start of the instructions.
4898 void* code_start;
4899 // Size of the instructions.
4900 size_t code_len;
4901 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
4902 Handle<UnboundScript> script;
4903 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
4904 // code line information which is returned from the
4905 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
4906 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
4907 void* user_data;
4908
4909 struct name_t {
4910 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
4911 // zero-terminated.
4912 const char* str;
4913 // Number of chars in str.
4914 size_t len;
4915 };
4916
4917 struct line_info_t {
4918 // PC offset
4919 size_t offset;
4920 // Code postion
4921 size_t pos;
4922 // The position type.
4923 PositionType position_type;
4924 };
4925
4926 union {
4927 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
4928 struct name_t name;
4929
4930 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
4931 struct line_info_t line_info;
4932
4933 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
4934 void* new_code_start;
4935 };
4936};

6063template <class T>
6064class Maybe {
6065 public:
6066 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value; }
6067 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value; }
6068
6069 // Will crash when checks are enabled if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6070 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6071#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
6072 V8::CheckIsJust(IsJust());
6073#endif
6074 return value;
6075 }
6076
6077 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6078 return has_value ? value : default_value;
6079 }
6080
6081 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6082 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6083 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6084 }
6085
6086 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6087 return !operator==(other);
6088 }
6089
6090 private:
6091 Maybe() : has_value(false) {}
6092 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value(true), value(t) {}
6093
6094 bool has_value;
6095 T value;
6096
6097 template <class U>
6098 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
6099 template <class U>
6100 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
6101};
6102
6103
6104template <class T>
6105inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
6106 return Maybe<T>();
6107}
6108
6109
6110template <class T>
6111inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
6112 return Maybe<T>(t);
6113}

6590const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
6591const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
6592const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
6593
6594// Tag information for HeapObject.
6595const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
6596const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
6597const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
6598
6599// Tag information for Smi.
6600const int kSmiTag = 0;
6601const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
6602const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
6603
6604template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
6605
6606template<int kSmiShiftSize>
6607V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6608 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6609 uintptr_t tagged_value =
6610 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
6611 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
6612}
6613
6614// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
6615template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
6616 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
6617 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
6618 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
6619 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
6620 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6621 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
6622 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
6623 }
6624 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6625 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
6626 }
6627 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
6628 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
6629 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
6630 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
6631 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
6632 //
6633 // CAUTION: The original code below:
6634 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
6635 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
6636 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
6637 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
6638 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
6639 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
6640 }
6641};
6642
6643// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
6644template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
6645 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
6646 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
6647 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
6648 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
6649 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6650 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
6651 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
6652 }
6653 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6654 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
6655 }
6656 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
6657 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
6658 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
6659 }
6660};
6661
6662typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
6663const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
6664const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
6665V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
6666V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

6772 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj, int shift) {
6773 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
6774 return *addr & static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);

6777 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeFlag(internal::Object** obj,
6778 bool value, int shift) {
6779 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
6780 uint8_t mask = static_cast<uint8_t>(1U << shift);
6781 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~mask) | (value << shift));
6782 }

6784 V8_INLINE static uint8_t GetNodeState(internal::Object** obj) {

6786 return *addr & kNodeStateMask;
6787 }

6789 V8_INLINE static void UpdateNodeState(internal::Object** obj,
6790 uint8_t value) {
6791 uint8_t* addr = reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(obj) + kNodeFlagsOffset;
6792 *addr = static_cast<uint8_t>((*addr & ~kNodeStateMask) | value);
6793 }

6823 template <typename T>
6824 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
6825 typedef internal::Object O;
6826 typedef internal::Internals I;
6827 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
6828 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
6829 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
6830 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
6831 int value_offset =
6832 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
6833 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
6834 }

7122template<typename T>
7123void ReturnValue<T>::Set(uint32_t i) {
7124 TYPE_CHECK(T, Integer);
7125 // Can't simply use INT32_MAX here for whatever reason.
7126 bool fits_into_int32_t = (i & (1U << 31)) == 0;
7127 if (V8_LIKELY(fits_into_int32_t)) {
7128 Set(static_cast<int32_t>(i));
7129 return;
7130 }
7131 Set(Integer::NewFromUnsigned(GetIsolate(), i));
7132}

7134template<typename T>
7135void ReturnValue<T>::Set(bool value) {
7136 TYPE_CHECK(T, Boolean);
7137 typedef internal::Internals I;
7138 int root_index;
7139 if (value) {
7140 root_index = I::kTrueValueRootIndex;
7141 } else {
7142 root_index = I::kFalseValueRootIndex;
7143 }
7144 *value_ = *I::GetRoot(GetIsolate(), root_index);
7145}

7326
7327Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
7328#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7329 typedef internal::Object O;
7330 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
7331 typedef internal::Internals I;
7332 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7333 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7334 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7335 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType) {
7336 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7337 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
7338 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
7339 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
7340 }
7341#endif
7342 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
7343}
7344
7345
7346void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
7347#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7348 typedef internal::Object O;
7349 typedef internal::Internals I;
7350 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7351 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7352 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7353 if (V8_LIKELY(I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType)) {
7354 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7355 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
7356 }
7357#endif
7358 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
7359}

7379String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
7380 typedef internal::Object O;
7381 typedef internal::Internals I;
7382 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
7383 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
7384 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
7385 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
7386 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
7387 } else {
7388 result = NULL;

7390#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7391 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
7392#endif
7393 return result;

7396
7397String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
7398 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
7399 typedef internal::Object O;
7400 typedef internal::Internals I;
7401 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
7402 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
7403 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
7404 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
7405 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
7406 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
7407 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
7408 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
7409 }
7410#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7411 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
7412#endif
7413 return resource;

7852
7853int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
7854 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
7855 typedef internal::Internals I;
7856 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory =
7857 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
7858 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset);
7859 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc =
7860 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
7861 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
7862 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset);
7863 int64_t amount = *amount_of_external_allocated_memory + change_in_bytes;
7864 if (change_in_bytes > 0 &&
7865 amount - *amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc >
7866 I::kExternalAllocationLimit) {
7867 CollectAllGarbage("external memory allocation limit reached.");
7868 }
7869 *amount_of_external_allocated_memory = amount;
7870 return *amount_of_external_allocated_memory;
7871}

7901Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
7902#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7903 typedef internal::Object O;
7904 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
7905 typedef internal::Internals I;
7906 HO* context = *reinterpret_cast<HO**>(this);
7907 O** result =
7908 HandleScope::CreateHandle(context, I::ReadEmbedderData<O*>(this, index));
7909 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
7910#else
7911 return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
7912#endif
7913}
